    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "D&C",
        "delineation": "Section",
        "number": 137,
        "summary": "1\u20136, The Prophet sees his brother Alvin in the celestial kingdom; 7\u20139, The doctrine of salvation for the dead is revealed; 10, All children are saved in the celestial kingdom.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The heavens were opened upon us, and I beheld the celestial kingdom of God, and the glory thereof, whether in the body or out I cannot tell.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 7:56 (55\u201356); 1\u00a0Ne. 1:8; Hel. 5:48 (45\u201349). TG\u00a0Heaven.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:43.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Celestial Glory; Kingdom of God, in Heaven.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 12:2 (2\u20134); Rev. 21:10; 1\u00a0Ne. 11:1; Moses 1:11.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I saw the transcendent beauty of the gate through which the heirs of that kingdom will enter, which was like unto circling flames of fire;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 21:19 (10\u201327); D&C 76:70. TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:41.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 24:17; Isa. 33:14 (14\u201315); Hel. 5:23; D&C 130:7; 133:41.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 1:4 (4\u201325).",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Also the blazing throne of God, whereon was seated the Father and the Son.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 1:27 (26\u201327); Dan. 7:9.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 6:1; Ezek. 1:26 (26\u201328); D&C 76:108 (106\u20138).",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godhead; God the Father, Elohim.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 7:55 (55\u201356).",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I saw the beautiful streets of that kingdom, which had the appearance of being paved with gold.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 21:21 (10\u201327); D&C 110:2.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I saw Father Adam and Abraham; and my father and my mother; my brother Alvin, that has long since slept;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adam.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 132:29; Abr. 2:11 (9\u201311).",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 124:19. TG\u00a0Family, Eternal.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:4.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 15:20.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 286
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And marveled how it was that he had obtained an inheritance in that kingdom, seeing that he had departed this life before the Lord had set his hand to gather Israel the second time, and had not been baptized for the remission of sins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 138:25.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation for the Dead.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 11:11; 1\u00a0Ne. 22:12 (10\u201312); Jacob 6:2. TG\u00a0Israel, Gathering of; Israel, Restoration of.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 157
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 24:47; John 3:5 (3\u20135); 2\u00a0Ne. 9:23; Ether 4:18 (18\u201319); D&C 76:52 (50\u201352); 84:74. TG\u00a0Baptism, Essential.",
                        "start": 199,
                        "end": 207
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus came the voice of the Lord unto me, saying: All who have died without a knowledge of this gospel, who would have received it if they had been permitted to tarry, shall be heirs of the celestial kingdom of God;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 5:30. TG\u00a0Revelation.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Pet. 4:6; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:26 (25\u201326); Mosiah 15:24; D&C 29:50.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 9:15 (14\u201315); D&C 76:70 (50\u201370). TG\u00a0Exaltation; Salvation for the Dead.",
                        "start": 176,
                        "end": 181
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Also all that shall die henceforth without a knowledge of it, who would have received it with all their hearts, shall be heirs of that kingdom;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 18:32; D&C 6:16.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I, the Lord, will judge all men according to their works, according to the desire of their hearts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 20:12 (12\u201314). TG\u00a0God, Justice of; Judgment, the Last.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works; Justice.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 64:22 (22, 34). TG\u00a0Agency; Motivations.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I also beheld that all children who die before they arrive at the years of accountability are saved in the celestial kingdom of heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 68:27 (25\u201327).",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation of Little Children.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}